                <note rend="inline" type="source">651G.11251/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hong Kong</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Southard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hong Kong</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-22">December 22,
                            1938</date>.<lb/>[Received December 22—12:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following telegram has been received from the American Consul at Saigon.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“December 22, 11 a.m. Restrictions on transit automobiles and trucks by road
                        from French Indo-China into China removed by order of the Governor General
                        made known orally last night. Only transit and registration taxes
                        required.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Repeated to Chungking, Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Southard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
